cs.CG, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.HC. 

The paper discusses techniques for automatically placing external labels on graphical displays and visualizations, which involves algorithms for geometric computation, graph drawing, computer vision, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GR (Graphics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) for their relevance to image processing and optimization. Finally, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible sub-category due to the focus on user-centered design and evaluation of labeling techniques.
